Hoodlums on Wednesday defied the curfew imposed in the state by Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu, destroying many public and private properties as the #EndSARS protest took a dangerous turn.



 


One of the buildings torched is the Headquarters of the Nation Newspaper on Fatai  Atere street in Ladipo area of the state.
The hoodlums allegedly invaded the media house, sent all the staff away and set the building on fire.
The hoodlums had earlier attacked the NPA facility in Dockyard, Apapa and the headquarters at Marina, burning the 9-storey building completely.
Also attacked were the Lekki-Ikoyi Bridge Toll Gate, the Oba’s palace in Lagos, the Oriental Hotel in Lekki, the TVC headquarters in Ikosi, the family homes of Governor Babajide Sanwo-Olu.
Many police stations have also been torched in Lagos, along with the council office of Ajeromi-Ifelodun Local Government.






